reviews.review_text:
Nak 300 Shotguns v. Healy Authorized AUD:  Dead Heat. Upon an initial, quick comparison, I find both AUDs well recorded with excellent dynamics.  In fact, I thought they might be the same source at first.  But after hearing a slight level fluctuation in Minglewood in the Healy AUD, and none in the Nak 300, I guess they aren't.  I'm really impressed with this source.

Nice job again Mr. Mow et al.  Five stars for sound.  Though this is a very good show, as per my Healy review, I think the song selection for the end of the show is less than the hoped for five star blowout.  4 1/2 Stars for this one.
Five Stars Doug Mow taped this one, not Jeff Silberman and gets all the credit.

Great show from an underappreciated year A very good show, indeed, for 1981. Jerry was on top of all his solos, despite that I believe he was at the height of his smoking heroin days here. A lot of energy in this show. Those Yale kids must've loved it. Great stuff.
To Lay Me Down Great recording, but missing To Lay Me Down in set 2.

good crowd The first set is fine. Scarlet, TLMD and The Wheel are excellent. Count me in for '81 shows, but no further.
The audio is a testament to a fine recording job.
